For the past 6 months I&#039;ve stopped playing LoL after having this problem. I have around 30-40 ping average and 200-400 FPS average, but for some reason my game always trips out and starts freezing up, I can still click around and move around the map. For example, I&#039;m in a 1v1 against Ekko as Riven, if I were to Q all I would see on my screen would be Riven moving forward without animation and Ekko&#039;s health bar deplete (sometimes nothing happens at all). 
My current specs are, Intel i5 6600k, EVGA GTX 1070 SC and an ASUS Z170 PRO GAMING. Any feedback/Help is appreciated {{summoner:13}}

EDIT: Capping FPS at 60 does seem to weaken the lag, but only by a bit.
